                  panels rendered in default  panels not needed for this
                  order. System functional,   specific case. No
                  less optimized.             AI-suggested emphasis.

  **Member Hub    All cards displayed in      All cards visible
  (CSR)**         fixed default order. Member regardless of member
                  lookup and card navigation  situation. DRO card shows
                  fully functional.           for all members (empty if
                                              no DRO). Ordering is
                                              generic, not contextual.

  **Scenario      Scenario Modeler rendered   Full scenario modeling
  (Counselor)**   with all calculation        capability. Less intuitive
                  options. No AI-optimized    layout but all
                  layout. Full calculation    functionality available.
                  accuracy.                   

  **Team          Static aggregate views from Stale data possible
  Dashboard**     most recent cache. No       (staleness indicator
                  intelligent prioritization  shown). All drill-down
                  signals. Manual refresh     navigation works.
                  required.                   Assignment and approval
                                              functions work.

  **Audit         Full audit functionality    Manual analysis required
  Workspace**     available. No AI-driven     where AI would normally
                  anomaly highlighting. All   flag outliers. All data
                  calculation re-verification access and export works.
                  works.                      

  **Employer      Full batch processing and   All contribution validation
  Dashboard**     validation. No AI-driven    and reconciliation works.
                  exception prioritization.   Exception list is not
                                              prioritized by likely
                                              severity.
  --------------- --------------------------- ---------------------------

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| **Key Principle (Reinforced)**                                        |
|                                                                       |
| *No workspace variant requires AI to function correctly. AI improves  |
| the experience through intelligent ordering, contextual emphasis, and |
| anomaly detection. At every degradation level, the data is accurate,  |
| the calculations are correct, and the functions work. What changes is |
| how efficiently information is organized and presented.*              |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+

**7. Role-Based Access Control Implications**

Each workspace variant requires specific RBAC permissions. The security
architecture (noui-security-architecture.md) defines RBAC + ABAC
controls; this section maps workspace variants to permission
requirements.

  ---------------- --------------------- ------------------ -----------------
  **Workspace**    **Read Permissions**  **Write            **Special
                                         Permissions**      Access**

  **CSR Hub**      All member data       Contact info       Member search by
                   (excluding            changes,           any identifier
                   medical/disability)   interaction        
                                         logging, work item 
                                         creation           

  **Counselor**    All member data +     Saved estimates,   Scenario model
                   estimate history      appointment notes  parameters

  **Benefits       Assigned case data    Case processing,   Claim/unclaim
  Analyst**        only                  calculations,      work items
                                         determinations     

  **Supervisor**   All team cases +      Approve, reject,   Team queue
                   operational metrics   reassign, annotate management

  **QA /           All cases             Audit findings,    Cross-case
  Compliance**     (historical), full    quality notes      queries, sampling
                   audit trails                             

  **Employer       Employer data, member Contribution batch Employer-level
  Services**       roster (non-PII)      processing         search

  **Finance**      Financial aggregates, Payment            Batch payment
                   payment records       authorization,     operations
                                         adjustments        

  **Executive**    Operational KPIs,     None (read-only    Drill-down to
                   aggregate data only   dashboard)         anonymized
                                                            details
  ---------------- --------------------- ------------------ -----------------

**Critical note:** The Benefits Analyst role has the most restrictive
data scope by design. Analysts see only their assigned cases, not the
full member database. This prevents unauthorized browsing and supports
audit trail integrity. The CSR role has broader read access because they
must respond to any member who calls, but has narrower write access
(limited to contact changes and work item creation, not case
processing).

**8. POC Scope and Phasing**

The DERP POC cannot implement all workspace variants simultaneously. The
following phasing aligns with the existing build plan.

**8.1 POC Deliverables (In Scope)**

-   **Task Workspace** --- Already the primary focus. The four demo
    cases prove composition for the Benefits Analyst role.

-   **Member Context Hub (CSR) --- Prototype** --- Demonstrate the
    alternative entry point with member lookup and navigation cards. Use
    the four demo cases to show how cards adapt per member situation.

-   **Composition Validation** --- Implement the deterministic validator
    for service retirement compositions. Demonstrate that incorrect
    compositions are caught and corrected.

-   **Static Fallback** --- Demonstrate degradation from composed
    workspace to static fallback for both Task and Hub variants.

**8.2 Post-POC Roadmap**

-   Scenario Workspace (Counselor variant) --- First post-POC addition,
    high member impact

-   Team Dashboard (Supervisor variant) --- Required for production
    operational management

-   Audit Workspace (QA/Compliance) --- Required before SOC 2 readiness

-   Employer Dashboard --- Phase 2, when employer integration is added

-   Executive Dashboard --- Phase 2, alongside operational analytics

-   Composition drift detection --- Requires production volume for
    baseline establishment

**9. What This Document Is Not**

This document does not define the visual design of any workspace
variant. Visual design language is defined in the Dynamic Workspace UX
Architecture document and applies consistently across all variants.

This document does not define the component library. Components
(MemberBanner, SalaryTable, BenefitCalculationPanel, etc.) are defined
in the Architecture Reference and are shared across all workspace
variants.

This document does not replace ADR-007. The degradation hierarchy
remains the governing specification for failure handling. This document
extends it with composition integrity monitoring and role-specific
fallback definitions.

This document does not define process workflows. How a retirement
application moves through stages is defined by the Process Orchestrator.
This document defines how different roles interact with those processes
through their specialized workspace variants.

*End of Document*
